,\"content\":[{\"id\":\"call_SyyX2PLKiHTBJ79KjGq1POBY\",\"arguments\":\"{\\\"path\\\": \\\"tests/fail_to_pass/nested_compound_model_issue.md\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"## Issue Summary\\\\nModeling's `separability_matrix` does not compute separability correctly for nested CompoundModels.\\\\n\\\\n## Steps to Reproduce\\\\n1. Import the necessary modules:\\\\n    ```python\\\\n    from astropy.modeling import models as m\\\\n    from astropy.modeling.separable import separability_matrix\\\\n    ```\\\\n2. Create the basic compound model:\\\\n    ```python\\\\n    cm = m.Linear1D(10) & m.Linear1D(5)\\\\n    print(separability_matrix(cm))  # Should output a diagonal matrix.\\\\n    ```\\\\n3. Create a more complex model:\\\\n    ```python\\\\n    complex_model = m.Pix2Sky_TAN() & cm\\\\n    print(separability_matrix(complex_model))  # Fails to produce expected separability.\\\\n    ```\\\\n\\\\n## Observed Behavior\\\\nThe output for the nested compound model incorrectly indicates non-separability:\\\\n```python\\\\narray([[ True,  True, False, False],\\\\n       [ True,  True, False, False],\\\\n       [False, False,  True,  True],\\\\n       [False, False,  True,  True]])\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n## Expected Behavior\\\\nThe output should indicate that the inputs and outputs of the linear models are separable and independent, similar to the simpler models.\\\\n\\\\n## Fail-to-pass Tests\\\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model6-result6]`\\\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model9-result9]`\\\\n\\\\n## Additional Information\\\\nThis seems to be a bug that needs further investigation.\\\"}\",\"name\":\"board_write_file\"},{\"id\":\"call_CbgKtpCkHoL7kUu8FQR1yCnQ\",\"arguments\":\"{\\\"path\\\": \\\"tests/fail_to_pass/README.md\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"# Fail-to-Pass Test Cases\\\\nThis directory contains details of tests that currently fail, highlighting issues in the code.\\\\n\\\\n## Current Failures\