])\\n```\\n\\n## Expected Behavior\\nThe output should indicate that the inputs and outputs of the linear models are separable and independent, similar to the simpler models.\\n\\n## Fail-to-pass Tests\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model6-result6]`\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model9-result9]`\\n\\n## Additional Information\\nThis seems to be a bug that needs further investigation."}', name='board_write_file'), FunctionCall(id='call_6s87BLsdjGBXMFtYYLB3Z1Ew', arguments='{"path": "fail_to_pass/README.md", "content": "# Fail-to-Pass Test Cases\\nThis directory contains details of tests that currently fail, highlighting issues in the code.\\n\\n## Current Failures\\n1. `separability_matrix` fails for nested compound models.\\n2. Reference the individual issue files for details."}', name='board_write_file')], results=[FunctionExecutionResult(content='Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/fail_to_pass/nested_compound_model_issue.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board', name='board_write_file', call_id='call_flkUxYyD8pKhfAs84nrtmzwh', is_error=False), FunctionExecutionResult(content='Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/fail_to_pass/README.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board', name='board_write_file', call_id='call_6s87BLsdjGBXMFtYYLB3Z1Ew', is_error=False)])}
