r\\\\nThe output should indicate that the inputs and outputs of the linear models are separable and independent, similar to the simpler models.\\\\n\\\\n## Fail-to-pass Tests\\\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model6-result6]`\\\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model9-result9]`\\\\n\\\\n## Additional Information\\\\nThis seems to be a bug that needs further investigation.\\\"}\",\"name\":\"board_write_file\"},{\"id\":\"call_ThLOO7ZIDj88LBJEQKRRQnJC\",\"arguments\":\"{\\\"path\\\": \\\"README.md\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"# Nested Compound Model Bug\\\\nThis document summarizes the issues related to the `separability_matrix` in nested compound models.\\\"}\",\"name\":\"board_write_file\"}],\"results\":[{\"content\":\"Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/nested_compound_issue.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board\",\"name\":\"board_write_file\",\"call_id\":\"call_X8rk75QzhxPjwW1oqWAnFLP1\",\"is_error\":false},{\"content\":\"Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/README.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board\",\"name\":\"board_write_file\",\"call_id\":\"call_ThLOO7ZIDj88LBJEQKRRQnJC\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"inner_messages\":[{\"id\":\"18173cc6-27c0-4be8-a772-bc84bda5340e\",\"source\":\"ProjectManager\",\"models_usage\":{\"prompt_tokens\":5310,\"completion_tokens\":443},\"metadata\":{},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-05T16:00:36.447954Z\",\"content\":[{\"id\":\"call_X8rk75QzhxPjwW1oqWAnFLP1\",\"arguments\":\"{\\\"path\\\": \\\"nested_compound_issue.md\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"## Issue Summary\\\\nModeling's `separability_matrix` does not compute separability correctly for nested CompoundModels.\\\\n\\\\n## Steps to Reproduce\\\\n1. Import the necessary modules:\\\\n    ```python\\\\n    from astropy.modeling import models as m\\\\n    from astropy.modeling.separable import separability_matrix\\\\n    ```\\\\n2. Create the basic compound model:\\\\n    ```python\\\\n    cm = m.Linear1D(10) & m.Linear1D(5)\\\\n    print(separability_matrix(cm))  # Should output a diagonal matrix.\\\\n    ```\\\\n3. Create a more complex model:\\\\n    ```python\\\\n    complex_model = m.Pix2Sky_TAN() & cm\\\\n    print(separability_matrix(complex_model))  # Fails to produce expected separability.\\\\n    ```\\\\n\\\\n## Observed Behavior\\\\nThe output for the nested compound model incorrectly indicates non-separability:\\\\n```python\\\\narray([[ True,  True, False, False],\\\\n       [ True,  True, False, False],\\\\n       [False, False,  True,  True],\\\\n       [False, False,  True,  True]])\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n## Expected Behavior\\\\nThe output should indicate that the inputs and outputs of the linear models are separable and independent, similar to the simpler models.\\\\n\\\\n## Fail-to-pass Tests\\\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model6-result6]`\\\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model9-result9]`\\\\n\\\\n## Additional Information\\\\nThis seems to be a bug that needs further investigation.\\\"}\",\"name\":\"board_write_file\"},{\"id\":\"call_ThLOO7ZIDj88LBJEQKRRQnJC\",\"arguments\":\"{\\\"path\\\": \\\"README.md\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"# Nested Compound Model Bug\\\\nThis document summarizes the issues related to the `separability_matrix` in nested compound models.\\\"}\",\"name\":\"board_write_file\"}],\"type\":\"ToolCallRequestEvent\"},{\"id\":\"b15f421c-b9f1-4d39-9450-1ae17eca3d30\",\"source\":\"ProjectManager\",\"models_usage\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-05T16:00:36.459560Z\",\"content\":[{\"content\":\"Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/ma