    [False, False,  True,  True],\\n       [False, False,  True,  True]])\\n```\\n\\n## Expected Behavior\\nThe output should indicate that the inputs and outputs of the linear models are separable and independent, similar to the simpler models.\\n\\n## Fail-to-pass Tests\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model6-result6]`\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model9-result9]`\\n\\n## Additional Information\\nThis seems to be a bug that needs further investigation.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_ThLOO7ZIDj88LBJEQKRRQnJC", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"README.md\", \"content\": \"# Nested Compound Model Bug\\nThis document summarizes the issues related to the `separability_matrix` in nested compound models.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/nested_compound_issue.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_X8rk75QzhxPjwW1oqWAnFLP1"}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/README.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_ThLOO7ZIDj88LBJEQKRRQnJC"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-DcCUHaqepZfh4P6uEdodN8W12COyU", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "tool_calls", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": "It seems there are multiple attempts to create directories and files to track the nested compound model bug in the `separability_matrix` computation, but there seems to be a consistent issue with directory access. \n\nHere\u2019s the structured plan to break down the original issue into s