_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": "It seems there are multiple attempts to create directories and files to track the nested compound model bug in the `separability_matrix` computation, but there seems to be a consistent issue with directory access. \n\nHere\u2019s the structured plan to break down the original issue into smaller actionable tickets:\n\n1. **Diagnosis of the buggy behavior in `separability_matrix`:**\n   - Create a diagnosis ticket to investigate why the `separability_matrix` fails for nested compound models.\n\n2. **Test Review:**\n   - Create a ticket to review the existing fail-to-pass tests related to `separability_matrix` in the `tests/test_separable.py` file.\n\n3. **Implementation Plan:**\n   - Create an implementation ticket to fix the issue with `separability_matrix` concerning nested CompoundModels.\n\n4. **Validation Strategy:**\n   - Create a QA ticket to validate that the changes made resolve the bug and do not introduce new issues.\n\n5. **Documentation Update:**\n   - Create a ticket to update any relevant documentation reflecting the changes made.\n\nNow, I will proceed to create the necessary tickets on the project board for each of these steps."}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/diagnosis/nested_compound_model_issue.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_XWwGtd5WigqPxJFfHGItVYiW"}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/tests/review_fail_to_pass_tests.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_8dYWuTOnBYzDpOEWboJAqLUC"}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralize