nt", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_BCRYpybHUlE1K9iQUdRDTWSZ", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"tests/fail_to_pass\"}", "name": "board_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/tests/fail_to_pass not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_BCRYpybHUlE1K9iQUdRDTWSZ"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_uTe1as8YBdHpvkmjvpEL85Ji", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"fail_to_pass/nested_compound_model_issue.md\", \"content\": \"## Issue Summary\\nModeling's `separability_matrix` does not compute separability correctly for nested CompoundModels.\\n\\n## Steps to Reproduce\\n1. Import the necessary modules:\\n    ```python\\n    from astropy.modeling import models as m\\n    from astropy.modeling.separable import separability_matrix\\n    ```\\n2. Create the basic compound model:\\n    ```python\\n    cm = m.Linear1D(10) & m.Linear1D(5)\\n    print(separability_matrix(cm))  # Should output a diagonal matrix.\\n    ```\\n3. Create a more complex model:\\n    ```python\\n    complex_model = m.Pix2Sky_TAN() & cm\\n    print(separability_matrix(complex_model))  # Fails to produce expected separability.\\n    ```\\n\\n## Observed Behavior\\nThe output for the nested compound model incorrectly indicates non-separability:\\n```python\\narray([[ True,  True, False, False],\\n       [ True,  True, False, False],\\n       [False, False,  True,  True],\\n       [False, False,  True,  True]])\\n```\\n\\n## Expected Behavior\\nThe output should indicate that the inputs and outputs of the linear models are separable and independent, similar to the simpler models.\\n\\n## Fail-to-pass Tests\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model6-result6]`\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model9-result9]`\\n\\n## Additional Information\\nThis seems to be a bug that needs further investigation.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_3fpbN4gOBKOSwNMyRJrjcErm", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"fail_to_pass/README.md\", \"content\": \"# Fail-to-Pass Test Cases\\nThis directory contains details of tests that currently fail, highlighting issues in the code.\\n\\n## Current Failures\\n1. `separability_matrix` fails for nested compound models.\\n2. Reference the individual issue files for details.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/fail_to_pass/nested_compound_model_issue.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_uTe1as8YBdHpvkmjvpEL85Ji"}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/fail_to_pass/README.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_3fpbN4gOBKOSwNMyRJrjcErm"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_rutvE8VUEA1cwWW0tgTSEIh0", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"nested_compound_model\"}", "name": "board_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/nested_compound_model not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_rutvE8VUEA1cwWW0tgTSEIh0"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_eaW1N659mtNIv8alrT5DwGnO", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"fail_to_pass