    [False, False,  True,  True],\\n       [False, False,  True,  True]])\\n```\\n\\n## Expected Behavior\\nThe output should indicate that the inputs and outputs of the linear models are separable and independent, similar to the simpler models.\\n\\n## Fail-to-pass Tests\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model6-result6]`\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model9-result9]`\\n\\n## Additional Information\\nThis seems to be a bug that needs further investigation.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_ThLOO7ZIDj88LBJEQKRRQnJC", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"README.md\", \"content\": \"# Nested Compound Model Bug\\nThis document summarizes the issues related to the `separability_matrix` in nested compound models.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/nested_compound_issue.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_X8rk75QzhxPjwW1oqWAnFLP1"}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/README.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_ThLOO7ZIDj88LBJEQKRRQnJC"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_XWwGtd5WigqPxJFfHGItVYiW", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"diagnosis/nested_compound_model_issue.md\", \"content\": \"## Diagnosis for Nested Compound Model Issue\\n- **Issue**: The `separability_matrix` does not compute the separability correctly for nested CompoundModels.\\n- **Required Investigation**: Analyze the existing implementation of `separability_matrix` to understand the logic and where it breaks when handling nested models. Gather and document the results.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_8dYWuTOnBYzDpOEWboJAqLUC", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"tests/review_fail_to_pass_tests.md\", \"content\": \"## Review of Fail-to-Pass Tests\\n- **Objective**: Review the tests in `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py` that currently fail:\\n  - `test_separable[compound_model6-result6]`\\n  - `test_separable[compound_model9-result9]`\\n- **Expected Outcome**: Determine whether the failures are due to a bug in the implementation of `separability_matrix` and suggest needed changes.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_MFtiRpZDoO3bwObSyon9yjO7", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"implementation/fix_separability_matrix.md\", \"content\": \"## Implementation Task: Fix separability_matrix\\n- **Task**: Update the logic in `separability_matrix` to correctly handle nested CompoundModels.\\n- **Success Criteria**: The function should return the expected diagonal format when dealing with separable inputs and outputs.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_tjRsjZgImFapgDMcnOg9zuzu", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"qa/validation_of_fix.md\", \"content\": \"## QA Validation for Nested Compound Model Fix\\n- **Objective**: Validate the implemented fix for `separability_matrix`. Ensure that tests related to nested CompoundModels pass after the fix.\\n- **Tasks**:\\n  1. Run the modified tests.\\n  2. Document any new issues encountered.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_F6uMzxiP78JLaxq5iRtiVEsr", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"documentation/update_separability_matrix_docs.md\", \"content\": \"## Documentation Update for separability_matrix\\n- **Task**: Update documentation for `separability_matrix` to reflect any changes made during the fix. Include examples of nested CompoundModels.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": "It seems there are multiple attempts to create directories and files to track the nested compound model bug in the `separability_matrix` computation, but there seems to be a consistent issue with directory access. \n\nHere\u2019s the structured plan to break down the original issue into smaller actionable tickets:\n\n1. **Diagnosis of the buggy behavior in `separability_matrix`:**\n   - Create a diagnosis ticket to investigate why the `separability_matrix` fails for nested compound models.\n\n2. **Test Review:**\n   - Create a ticket to review the existing fail-to-pass tests related to `separability_matrix` in the `tests/test_separable.py` file.\n\n3. **Implementation Plan:**\n   - Create an implementation ticket to fix the issue with `separability_matrix` concerning nested CompoundModels.\n\n4. **Validation Strategy:**\n   - Create a QA ticket to validate that the changes made resolve the bug and do not introduce new issues.\n\n5. **Documentation Update:**\n   - Create a ticket to update any relevant documentation reflecting the changes made.\n\nNow, I will proceed to create the necessary tickets on the project board for each of these steps."}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/diagnosis/nested_compound_model_issue.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_XWwGtd5WigqPxJFfHGItVYiW"}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/tests/review_fail_to_pass_tests.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_8dYWuTOnBYzDpOEWboJAqLUC"}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralize