    [False, False,  True,  True],\\n       [False, False,  True,  True]])\\n```\\n\\n## Expected Behavior\\nThe output should indicate that the inputs and outputs of the linear models are separable and independent, similar to the simpler models.\\n\\n## Fail-to-pass Tests\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model6-result6]`\\n- `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model9-result9]`\\n\\n## Additional Information\\nThis seems to be a bug that needs further investigation.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_ThLOO7ZIDj88LBJEQKRRQnJC", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"README.md\", \"content\": \"# Nested Compound Model Bug\\nThis document summarizes the issues related to the `separability_matrix` in nested compound models.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/nested_compound_issue.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_X8rk75QzhxPjwW1oqWAnFLP1"}, {"content": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-decentralized/README.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_decentralized/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_ThLOO7ZIDj88LBJEQKRRQnJC"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_XWwGtd5WigqPxJFfHGItVYiW", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"diagnosis/nested_compound_model_issue.md\", \"content\": \"## Diagnosis for Nested Compound Model Issue\\n- **Issue**: The `separability_matrix` does not compute the separability correctly for nested CompoundModels.\\n- **Required Investigation**: Analyze the existing implementation of `separability_matrix` to understand the logic